WEBVTT

00:01.784 --> 00:03.829
<i>Previously</i> <i>
on</i> The Cleaning Lady...

00:03.873 --> 00:05.135
Brandon said he'll let us
work here

00:05.179 --> 00:06.310
if we sell a little E
on the side.

00:06.354 --> 00:08.747
Drugs? Fi, no.

00:08.791 --> 00:10.097
The donor backed out,

00:10.140 --> 00:12.055
and we've been waiting
for another match.

00:12.099 --> 00:13.317
I'm afraid we can't help you.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.145
I got Luca's results.

00:15.189 --> 00:16.320
I'm sorry, Thony.

00:16.364 --> 00:19.149
This disqualifies him
from the trial.

00:19.193 --> 00:21.064
Get out.

00:21.108 --> 00:22.152
Get out of here!

00:23.023 --> 00:24.546
What, are you scared of me now?

00:24.589 --> 00:26.113
You're not the man
I thought you were.

00:26.156 --> 00:27.853
You don't get to judge me

00:27.897 --> 00:29.899
and still take
from the fruits of my labor.

00:29.942 --> 00:32.206
I only did this
to help my family.

00:37.820 --> 00:39.126
<i>♪ I don't give a damn</i> <i>
'bout my reputation ♪</i>

00:39.169 --> 00:42.477
Leaving Las Vegas.
LA, here we come.

00:42.520 --> 00:43.956
- Snacks?
- Check.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.567
- Water?
- Check.

00:45.610 --> 00:47.003
Sob story?

00:47.047 --> 00:48.526
- Check.
- Mm-hmm.

00:48.570 --> 00:50.528
Is this crazy,
what I'm about to do?

00:50.572 --> 00:52.139
No crazier than me thinking
I can afford

00:52.182 --> 00:54.141
an immigration attorney
for Chris.

00:54.184 --> 00:56.099
At least it's an adventure,
you know,

00:56.143 --> 00:59.276
like Thelma and Louise
on the open road.

01:01.539 --> 01:03.106
Yeah, I remember
how they ended up.

01:03.150 --> 01:04.977
You can do this, Thony.

01:05.021 --> 01:06.370
I know you can
convince this idiot

01:06.414 --> 01:08.329
who backed out on Luca
to change his mind.

01:08.372 --> 01:10.113
Ah, if I'm allowed
to talk to the donor.

01:10.157 --> 01:12.942
No, when. Visualize it.

01:12.985 --> 01:15.205
Okay.

01:15.249 --> 01:19.035
First, I'm gonna convince
Dr. Ramtej to give me his info.

01:19.079 --> 01:20.993
I mean, he'd be saving
Luca's life.

01:21.037 --> 01:22.343
Who can say no to that?

01:22.386 --> 01:23.126
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:23.170 --> 01:25.389
<i>♪</i>

01:25.433 --> 01:28.175
Yeah!

01:28.218 --> 01:31.308
No, I'm sorry.

01:31.352 --> 01:34.224
I know how hard it was
when that donor backed out.

01:34.268 --> 01:35.921
But there was nothing
I could do then,

01:35.965 --> 01:37.836
and there's nothing
I can do now, Thony.

01:37.880 --> 01:40.970
Luca's liver was damaged
from an infection.

01:41.013 --> 01:43.320
If he can get
the bone marrow transplant now,

01:43.364 --> 01:45.148
his liver could repair,

01:45.192 --> 01:47.846
but without it,
he won't stand a chance.

01:47.890 --> 01:49.152
Thony, you know
I'm not allowed

01:49.196 --> 01:50.849
to give you
the donor's information.

01:52.373 --> 01:54.157
You could talk to him.

01:54.201 --> 01:56.159
Yeah, if he knew it was a kid,
he'd be a schmuck to say no.

01:56.203 --> 01:58.770
There are privacy laws
in place.

01:58.814 --> 02:00.772
I'm not allowed
to talk to him either.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.426
And even if I could,

02:02.470 --> 02:05.212
it says here he withdrew from
the donor registry altogether.

02:11.087 --> 02:12.306
I'm sorry,

02:12.349 --> 02:15.396
but my hands are tied.

02:18.399 --> 02:25.101
<i>♪</i>

02:27.277 --> 02:30.280
I'm not leaving here without
the donor's name and address.

02:32.064 --> 02:33.370
Hell yeah.

02:33.414 --> 02:35.242
We won't have much time.

02:37.244 --> 02:39.202
I hope he didn't
lock his office.

02:39.246 --> 02:41.813
Okay. Okay.

02:41.857 --> 02:45.817
If Dr. Ramtej comes back,
do something.

02:45.861 --> 02:47.471
Yeah, yeah, okay.

02:47.515 --> 02:49.604
<i>♪ Nobody knows</i> <i>
where I'ma head now ♪</i>

02:49.647 --> 02:52.215
<i>♪ The clock's tickin'</i> <i>
in the background ♪</i>

02:52.259 --> 02:54.696
<i>♪ Down to the minute,</i> <i>
I won't back out ♪</i>

02:54.739 --> 02:57.481
<i>♪ I said I'm never</i> <i>
lookin' back now ♪</i>

02:57.525 --> 02:59.918
<i>♪ Nobody knows</i> <i>
where I'ma head now ♪</i>

02:59.962 --> 03:02.617
Come on, come on.

03:02.660 --> 03:05.446
<i>♪ Down to the minute,</i> <i>
I won't back out ♪</i>

03:05.489 --> 03:06.925
<i>♪ I said I'm never</i> <i>
lookin' back now ♪</i>

03:06.969 --> 03:12.366
<i>♪</i>

03:12.409 --> 03:14.237
Thony, Thony.
Thony!

03:15.456 --> 03:16.979
Go.

03:18.633 --> 03:22.245
Dr. Ramtej.

03:22.289 --> 03:24.813
Thony's just in the restroom,
but I wanted to ask you,

03:24.856 --> 03:28.295
do you know anything
about migraines?

03:28.338 --> 03:32.255
Yeah, I've been having
this pain right here.

03:32.299 --> 03:33.822
Really,
I'm not a neurologist.

03:33.865 --> 03:38.348
No, I mean,
I've been using aspirin

03:38.392 --> 03:41.482
and ibuprofen, but I mean,
just nothing seems to work.

03:41.525 --> 03:44.441
You want to see if your doctor
can prescribe medication

03:44.485 --> 03:47.357
with naproxen or eletriptan.

03:48.184 --> 03:50.404
Wait, how do you spell it?

03:50.447 --> 03:52.362
I mean, I'll have
to write these down.

03:52.406 --> 03:54.277
I mean I'll never remember
these, let alone spell them.

03:56.148 --> 03:58.107
- Crap. Do you have a pen?
- Yes.

03:58.150 --> 04:00.196
<i>♪</i>

04:00.240 --> 04:02.503
<i>♪ Nobody knows</i> <i>
where I'ma head now ♪</i>

04:02.546 --> 04:05.375
<i>♪ The clock's tickin'</i> <i>
in the background ♪</i>

04:05.419 --> 04:06.942
<i>♪ Down to the minute,</i> <i>
I won't back out ♪</i>

04:06.985 --> 04:08.204
The first one is naproxen,

04:08.248 --> 04:12.295
which is N-A-P-R-O-X-E-N.

04:12.339 --> 04:14.341
- Uh-huh.
- And eletriptan.

04:14.384 --> 04:15.690
Okay.

04:15.733 --> 04:18.388
E-L-E-T-R-E--

04:18.432 --> 04:21.783
Great, thank you
so much, Doctor.

04:21.826 --> 04:24.481
- Yes.
- Yes. Oh, your pen.

04:24.525 --> 04:25.569
- Oh, thank you.
- Thank you. Bye.

04:25.613 --> 04:30.313
<i>♪</i>

04:36.537 --> 04:43.457
<i>♪</i>

04:47.548 --> 04:48.897
- Come on.
- 1613.

04:48.940 --> 04:50.377
Ooh, it's a nice house.

04:50.420 --> 04:52.204
Well, I mean,
at least he's Filipino,

04:52.248 --> 04:53.510
I mean, that should help.

04:56.383 --> 04:57.340
Mm-hmm.

05:00.648 --> 05:03.346
Hi, we're looking
for Joe Fabroa.

05:03.390 --> 05:04.521
Is he home?

05:04.565 --> 05:05.827
He doesn't live here anymore.

05:05.870 --> 05:07.785
Oh, really?

05:10.788 --> 05:12.573
Do you know
where we can find him?

05:12.616 --> 05:14.444
If you're asking for money
or something--

05:14.488 --> 05:17.012
No, no, no, it's not that.

05:17.055 --> 05:20.450
Oh, my son got sick,
and he agreed to help him.

05:20.494 --> 05:22.974
That doesn't sound
like my dad.

05:23.018 --> 05:26.456
Please. I wouldn't ask
if it wasn't an emergency.

05:27.849 --> 05:30.025
He works at West Coast
Premiere Automotive

05:30.068 --> 05:31.853
- in Santa Clarita.
- Okay.

05:31.896 --> 05:34.421
And please don't tell him
I told you.

05:35.552 --> 05:38.381
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you. Thank you.

05:40.470 --> 05:44.126
Santa Clarita.
Where's Santa Clarita?

05:45.432 --> 05:46.520
Ah, did you get
the jalapeño chips?

05:46.563 --> 05:49.349
- Ah, get your own.
- Not nice.

05:50.785 --> 05:52.221
You see the surveillance photos

05:52.264 --> 05:53.178
- of Knight yet?
- Mm-mm.

05:53.222 --> 05:54.484
I mean, what kind
of councilman

05:54.528 --> 05:55.833
gets that kind of ass?

05:55.877 --> 05:57.400
The kind
who can pay for it.

05:57.444 --> 05:58.836
Her name's Lexi Torres.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.490
She's a dancer at La Habana.

06:00.534 --> 06:03.667
She does twirly thing
from the scarves.

06:03.711 --> 06:06.583
- An aerialist?
- Yeah, whatever.

06:06.627 --> 06:09.499
Maybe we could use her
as our eyes inside the club.

06:09.543 --> 06:11.196
I've already got
someone for that.

06:11.240 --> 06:12.676
- Your cleaning lady?
- Right.

06:12.720 --> 06:14.548
Well, you seem
overly confident,

06:14.591 --> 06:16.593
considering she
didn't bring you squat

06:16.637 --> 06:17.812
from the Barsamian wedding.

06:17.855 --> 06:19.770
You know, Thony
is our direct link to Arman,

06:19.814 --> 06:21.076
but you're right;
I mean, if we could nab Knight

06:21.119 --> 06:22.556
for bribery
and make him talk,

06:22.599 --> 06:24.862
maybe ASAC Russo will stop
riding our asses.

06:24.906 --> 06:27.517
She's riding your ass,
Garrett, not mine.

06:29.606 --> 06:30.912
<i>MAN</i> <i>
Joe Fabroa,</i>

06:30.955 --> 06:32.609
<i>you have customers</i> <i>
in the showroom.</i>

06:32.653 --> 06:34.655
<i>- Joe Fabroa.</i>
- That's gotta be him.

06:34.698 --> 06:37.309
Look at that strut.
He's definitely Filipino.

06:41.531 --> 06:44.839
Ah, my Filipina sisters.
Mm-hmm.

06:44.882 --> 06:46.667
Looks like you found
the right man.

06:46.710 --> 06:48.669
All right, so just tell me
what you got your eye on,

06:48.712 --> 06:50.366
and I'll get you cruising'
out of here in no time.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.977
Thank you, Joe, but do you mind
if we talk in your office?

06:55.545 --> 06:58.635
Got financing concerns?
I got you, all right?

06:58.679 --> 06:59.810
Don't you worry about it.

06:59.854 --> 07:02.509
Come on.
Water or coffee?

07:02.552 --> 07:03.858
Oh, no, thank you.

07:03.901 --> 07:05.512
Oh, you sure about that?
It's not bad. Huh?

07:05.555 --> 07:07.644
We got one of those
pod machines.

07:07.688 --> 07:08.950
Okay.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.041
I hate to disappoint,

07:13.084 --> 07:16.653
but I don't really
speak to Tagalog.

07:16.697 --> 07:17.872
Oh.

07:17.915 --> 07:19.351
I mean, my Lola
used to call me her...

07:20.788 --> 07:22.964
But no other than that.

07:23.007 --> 07:24.705
Her stinky monkey?

07:27.751 --> 07:29.840
I thought it meant
her good boy.

07:32.408 --> 07:33.888
Well, then you're in luck,

07:33.931 --> 07:36.151
because today
you're getting the good boy.

07:36.194 --> 07:37.631
How can I help you?

07:37.674 --> 07:40.721
Wait, let me guess.
Sleek European model.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.288
Well, actually,

07:43.332 --> 07:45.682
there's something I need
to talk to you about.

07:45.726 --> 07:50.078
My son has a life-threatening
immune disorder.

07:50.121 --> 07:51.862
And we came here
from the Philippines

07:51.906 --> 07:54.299
for a bone marrow transplant.

07:54.343 --> 07:56.693
But the donor backed out.

07:56.737 --> 08:01.568
<i>♪</i>

08:01.611 --> 08:03.918
Is this some sort of joke?

08:05.397 --> 08:07.965
I came to ask if you would
please reconsider

08:08.009 --> 08:10.098
going through
with the donation.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.973
How the hell did you find me?

08:16.017 --> 08:20.804
Joe, my son's entire
immune system is broken.

08:22.284 --> 08:23.720
A simple cold could kill him.

08:23.764 --> 08:25.592
All right, look.

08:25.635 --> 08:28.682
I feel really bad for you.

08:28.725 --> 08:31.206
I do.
But this is not my problem.

08:31.249 --> 08:34.165
But, Joe, her son could die.

08:34.209 --> 08:35.819
So you just come here
to my place of work,

08:35.863 --> 08:36.994
and you corner me?

08:37.038 --> 08:38.213
I don't know you.

08:38.256 --> 08:40.563
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

08:40.607 --> 08:43.174
But you were the only match
for my son.

08:43.218 --> 08:44.741
No, I'm sorry.

08:44.785 --> 08:46.221
I'm sorry,
because I can't help you.

08:46.656 --> 08:49.616
Why did you sign up
as a donor in the first place?

08:49.659 --> 08:51.966
I didn't.
My daughter did.

08:52.009 --> 08:53.750
And she's not even
speaking to me anymore.

08:53.794 --> 08:55.796
Listen.

08:55.839 --> 08:59.843
I know it's not allowed,
but I can pay you.

08:59.887 --> 09:02.759
I don't have much, but--
Fine.

09:02.803 --> 09:05.370
You want my bone marrow?
It'll be 50 grand.

09:05.414 --> 09:07.677
You can't be serious.

09:07.721 --> 09:10.245
We're your <i>kabayan.</i>

09:10.288 --> 09:12.813
- We're your people.
- I was born in Reseda, okay?

09:12.856 --> 09:15.076
I'm as American
as the next guy.

09:15.119 --> 09:16.512
So don't come at me
with your problems

09:16.556 --> 09:19.428
just because I'm half Filipino.

09:19.471 --> 09:21.604
The procedure only takes
a few hours.

09:21.648 --> 09:24.738
Joe, please be reasonable.

09:24.781 --> 09:25.956
100 grand.

09:27.436 --> 09:28.959
And now you're
just being a dick.

09:32.484 --> 09:34.617
Yeah.

09:34.661 --> 09:37.838
I can play this game
all day.

09:37.881 --> 09:39.622
Trust me.

09:39.666 --> 09:41.842
You don't want
to negotiate with me.

09:41.885 --> 09:44.975
<i>♪</i>

09:45.019 --> 09:46.455
Now, if you don't have
the money,

09:46.498 --> 09:49.110
get the hell out of here
before I have you removed.

09:49.153 --> 09:53.636
<i>♪</i>

09:55.116 --> 10:01.818
<i>♪</i>

10:16.920 --> 10:18.443
I'm sorry, Thony.

10:18.487 --> 10:21.664
That wasn't exactly
the road trip we envisioned.

10:21.708 --> 10:23.927
It would have been more fun
to drive off the Grand Canyon.

10:23.971 --> 10:27.104
Wait, why are
all the lights off?

10:27.148 --> 10:28.540
Wait, did you see that?

10:29.890 --> 10:31.543
There's someone's inside.

10:35.896 --> 10:37.680
Thony. Oh, my God.

10:40.291 --> 10:42.293
Be careful.

10:42.337 --> 10:49.083
<i>♪</i>

10:53.087 --> 10:54.871
Wait!

10:56.743 --> 10:58.048
Okay, okay.
Wait.

10:58.092 --> 10:59.528
Be careful.

10:59.571 --> 11:05.752
<i>♪</i>

11:08.755 --> 11:09.930
Who's in there?

11:09.973 --> 11:12.802
<i>♪</i>

11:13.760 --> 11:15.544
Oh, God!

11:15.587 --> 11:17.154
You scared the crap
out of us!

11:17.198 --> 11:19.374
We're playing
flashlight tag.

11:19.417 --> 11:20.854
Yeah.

11:20.897 --> 11:22.159
Chill out.

11:22.203 --> 11:25.641
We were just having fun.
Remember that?

11:25.685 --> 11:27.121
So what took you guys so long?

11:27.164 --> 11:30.559
It was complicated.

11:30.602 --> 11:32.735
So no donor?

11:32.779 --> 11:35.738
Hi, Daddy, miss you.

11:35.782 --> 11:39.742
Figures.
Chris, not the time.

11:39.786 --> 11:41.352
I'm just saying,

11:41.396 --> 11:42.919
did you really have to drive
all the way to LA?

11:42.963 --> 11:44.442
Yes, we did,

11:44.486 --> 11:46.140
'cause if we didn't,
we'd always be asking ourselves

11:46.183 --> 11:49.143
if we did everything
we could, all right?

11:49.970 --> 11:51.580
Okay, jeez, sorry.

11:53.016 --> 11:54.801
Don't you have homework
or something?

12:08.902 --> 12:10.425
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

12:10.468 --> 12:13.994
You know there--
there's money I saved up.

12:14.037 --> 12:15.952
You should just take it
for Chris' attorney.

12:15.996 --> 12:17.649
Don't say that.

12:17.693 --> 12:20.565
Hey, you're gonna find a way
to get this transplant, Thony,

12:20.609 --> 12:23.568
and I'm gonna
figure out something too.

12:23.612 --> 12:25.266
I mean, maybe Brandon
will still let me

12:25.309 --> 12:26.833
work at the Golden Phoenix.

12:28.051 --> 12:29.705
Don't worry.

12:29.749 --> 12:31.925
I'm gonna give him back
his stash.

12:31.968 --> 12:33.796
I'm not gonna sell drugs, okay?

12:33.840 --> 12:36.886
I didn't say anything.
Hmm.

12:36.930 --> 12:38.670
You didn't have to.

12:42.065 --> 12:44.633
What are you gonna
tell Marco?

12:47.723 --> 12:49.943
The truth.

12:49.986 --> 12:51.814
Right back to square one.

12:55.339 --> 12:57.037
<i>Good night, kiddo.</i>

12:57.080 --> 12:59.822
<i>We'll play flashlight tag</i> <i>
when I see you next, okay?</i>

13:01.345 --> 13:02.869
Good night, Daddy.

13:04.435 --> 13:06.002
Okay.

13:06.046 --> 13:08.483
All right, peanut.

13:10.920 --> 13:13.053
Sleepy tight now, yeah?

13:13.096 --> 13:19.450
<i>♪</i>

13:19.494 --> 13:20.887
Hey.

13:20.930 --> 13:23.715
<i>He's pale.</i> <i>
His eyes look tired.</i>

13:23.759 --> 13:26.718
It's his liver.
It's getting worse.

13:26.762 --> 13:30.679
<i>I feel so helpless.</i>

13:30.722 --> 13:33.464
<i>I haven't held my son</i> <i>
in nearly a year.</i>

13:33.508 --> 13:34.944
<i>You have no idea</i> <i>
how that feels.</i>

13:37.120 --> 13:40.863
<i>If we're really</i> <i>
out of options,</i>

13:40.907 --> 13:42.647
<i>I need you</i> <i>
to bring home my son.</i>

13:42.691 --> 13:44.562
It's not gonna come
to that, Marco.

13:45.955 --> 13:47.914
I'm gonna figure out a way.

13:47.957 --> 13:50.438
I don't know how,
but I will.

13:50.481 --> 13:51.831
Okay?

13:54.050 --> 13:56.444
<i>Yeah, I pray.</i> <i>
I love you.</i>

13:56.487 --> 13:58.489
I love you.

13:58.533 --> 14:05.061
<i>♪</i>

14:06.280 --> 14:10.153
Hey, Brandon, it's Fiona.

14:10.197 --> 14:13.461
Wondering if we might
be able to meet up.

14:13.504 --> 14:15.115
Call me.

14:15.158 --> 14:21.904
<i>♪</i>

14:23.297 --> 14:24.515
Have a seat.

14:25.952 --> 14:28.302
I really need to get to work.

14:28.345 --> 14:30.957
Oh, don't worry.
This won't take long.

14:31.000 --> 14:33.829
So the walkies
were a big hit.

14:33.873 --> 14:36.266
The kids loved them.

14:36.310 --> 14:38.921
Sammy actually barely even
looked at the bike

14:38.965 --> 14:41.141
his mom got him, so hey,

14:41.184 --> 14:43.186
score one point for Dad, huh?

14:43.230 --> 14:44.840
Oh, that's good.

14:44.884 --> 14:46.929
So you went to Sammy's
birthday party after all.

14:46.973 --> 14:49.540
Solid advice.
You're very wise woman.

14:51.020 --> 14:52.108
Which is why I'm surprised

14:52.152 --> 14:54.328
that you're still
playing games with me.

14:54.371 --> 14:57.418
We both know that you're not
telling me everything, Thony.

14:57.461 --> 15:02.031
<i>♪</i>

15:02.075 --> 15:03.598
You recognize that guy?

15:03.641 --> 15:10.387
<i>♪</i>

15:12.999 --> 15:14.783
No.

15:14.826 --> 15:17.568
<i>♪</i>

15:20.441 --> 15:24.662
Thony, you remember
that little rule, hmm?

15:24.706 --> 15:26.882
Lying to a federal agent,
it's a felony.

15:26.926 --> 15:30.059
<i>♪</i>

15:30.103 --> 15:32.018
He's at the club
almost every day.

15:32.061 --> 15:34.585
He's Mr. Free Lunch.

15:34.629 --> 15:37.110
And I'd say by your
non-reaction reaction,

15:37.153 --> 15:39.025
you do recognize him.

15:39.068 --> 15:43.246
<i>♪</i>

15:43.290 --> 15:47.642
Hey, you remember Q, hmm?

15:47.685 --> 15:50.123
You know, James Bond, 007?

15:50.166 --> 15:51.602
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

15:51.646 --> 15:54.214
One of the cool things
about being in the FBI?

15:54.257 --> 16:01.177
<i>♪</i>

16:01.221 --> 16:02.918
All these little doodads
right here,

16:02.962 --> 16:05.268
they're actually
recording devices.

16:05.312 --> 16:08.228
So the next time that you see
Knight talking with Arman,

16:08.271 --> 16:11.057
all you gotta do is...

16:11.100 --> 16:13.059
and just drop it
under their table.

16:13.102 --> 16:15.191
Oh, no,
I don't think so.

16:15.235 --> 16:18.281
Oh, no. I'm not asking.

16:18.325 --> 16:22.677
<i>♪</i>

16:22.720 --> 16:25.723
What happens
if they see me do this?

16:25.767 --> 16:27.508
Oh, you just say, you know,

16:27.551 --> 16:31.860
"Whoopsie, I dropped my pen,"
you know, kind of like that.

16:31.903 --> 16:36.734
<i>♪</i>

16:36.778 --> 16:38.910
I will see after your shift.

16:38.954 --> 16:45.700
<i>♪</i>

16:54.143 --> 17:01.063
<i>♪</i>

17:11.943 --> 17:15.643
<i>♪</i>

17:15.686 --> 17:18.124
<i>
♪ Just let me see</i>

17:18.167 --> 17:19.429
<i>♪ Behind your skin,</i> <i>
what's hiding ♪</i>

17:19.473 --> 17:22.084
<i>♪ Believe me</i>

17:22.128 --> 17:24.260
<i>♪ I'm another one</i> <i>
who's dying ♪</i>

17:24.304 --> 17:26.175
<i>♪ Just let me see</i>

17:26.219 --> 17:28.090
<i>♪ Behind your skin,</i> <i>
what's hiding ♪</i>

17:28.134 --> 17:30.353
<i>♪ Believe me</i>

17:30.397 --> 17:32.312
<i>♪ I'm another one</i> <i>
who's dying ♪</i>

17:32.355 --> 17:33.443
<i>♪</i>

17:33.487 --> 17:36.142
Elaine.

17:36.185 --> 17:39.275
So you're Mr. Barsamian's
business partner?

17:39.319 --> 17:40.581
Oh, they're more
than business partners.

17:40.624 --> 17:42.670
Arman is like a son to him.

17:42.713 --> 17:44.367
He put the entire deal
together for Hayak.

17:44.411 --> 17:45.760
Our capitals lined up,

17:45.803 --> 17:48.023
and their gaming license
is preapproved.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.111
All we need is for your client

17:49.155 --> 17:51.113
to sell us
his hotel and casino.

17:51.157 --> 17:54.116
And Arman's definitely gonna
make it worth your while

17:54.160 --> 17:57.337
to convince him.

17:57.380 --> 17:58.773
You know, we all take care
of each other

17:58.816 --> 18:01.123
around here, Elaine.

18:01.167 --> 18:03.299
Well, you should know
I have Chinese investors

18:03.343 --> 18:04.909
waiting in the wings.

18:04.953 --> 18:07.956
Oh, trust me, Arman's offer
is going to be competitive.

18:07.999 --> 18:10.480
- Let me tell you that.
- It's like Eric says, Elaine.

18:10.524 --> 18:13.353
We take care of everyone
we deal with here.

18:13.396 --> 18:15.833
I will let you two
figure out those details.

18:17.226 --> 18:18.619
Excuse me one minute.

18:18.662 --> 18:23.928
<i>♪</i>

18:23.972 --> 18:24.799
Here's the details.

18:27.193 --> 18:31.632
<i>♪</i>

18:31.675 --> 18:33.982
Thony.

18:34.025 --> 18:35.810
A word, please.

18:38.813 --> 18:44.166
<i>♪</i>

18:44.210 --> 18:46.342
Look, I don't know if you've
done fine dining before,

18:46.386 --> 18:48.344
but you don't sweep the floor

18:48.388 --> 18:49.693
when the clients
are still present.

18:50.781 --> 18:52.566
Sorry, I wasn't thinking.

18:57.266 --> 18:59.181
What is it?

18:59.225 --> 19:01.401
Luca started his trial,
didn't he?

19:01.444 --> 19:03.881
No, he got kicked out
because of liver damage,

19:03.925 --> 19:05.318
so he can't be in it.

19:05.361 --> 19:07.015
So they care more
about the success of a trial

19:07.058 --> 19:08.016
than saving his life?

19:08.059 --> 19:10.410
Yeah.

19:10.453 --> 19:12.847
Well, now he needs
a liver transplant.

19:12.890 --> 19:15.850
But he can't get one until
his immune system is fixed.

19:15.893 --> 19:17.547
And the only possible
bone marrow donor

19:17.591 --> 19:18.809
is still being an ass.

19:18.853 --> 19:20.985
- You spoke to him?
- Yeah, yesterday.

19:21.029 --> 19:23.336
I tracked him down
to where he works.

19:25.076 --> 19:26.643
I stole his records
from the hospital.

19:28.863 --> 19:30.212
Well, that's a real
gangster move right there.

19:31.648 --> 19:33.084
Yeah.

19:33.128 --> 19:35.435
Well, even after I told him
about Luca,

19:35.478 --> 19:37.219
he still won't do it.

19:37.263 --> 19:38.873
Not unless I pay him
a lot of money.

19:38.916 --> 19:41.615
- How much money?
- $100,000.

19:41.658 --> 19:44.270
Seriously?
To save a kid's life?

19:44.313 --> 19:45.662
That's extortion.

19:45.706 --> 19:48.709
- How much do you have?
- Maybe $10,000.

19:50.101 --> 19:51.625
I'm not asking you
for the money.

19:51.668 --> 19:54.236
No, it's not about the money.
This guy's exploiting you.

19:56.325 --> 19:57.283
Let me talk to him.

19:59.502 --> 20:02.418
I know what happens
when you talk to someone.

20:02.462 --> 20:04.899
There's nothing I hate more
than people in power

20:04.942 --> 20:06.422
screwing over people in need,

20:06.466 --> 20:07.902
and that's what he's doing
to you right now.

20:09.991 --> 20:11.645
So do you want my help or not?

20:11.688 --> 20:18.434
<i>♪</i>

20:18.478 --> 20:21.132
Okay.

20:21.176 --> 20:23.091
Just don't hurt him.

20:23.134 --> 20:29.880
<i>♪</i>

20:34.972 --> 20:37.497
Fully loaded, power steering,
max torque,

20:37.540 --> 20:41.152
a premium sound system that
will blow your head off, okay?

20:41.196 --> 20:43.677
Zero to 60 in six.
She's a beaut, right?

20:45.592 --> 20:47.376
Eh, she's all right.

20:47.420 --> 20:48.725
I prefer my Caddy.

20:48.769 --> 20:51.162
Oh, come on.

20:51.206 --> 20:52.512
Caddies are for grandpas.

20:52.555 --> 20:54.340
A man of your style deserves
to be in something cool.

20:54.383 --> 20:55.906
What kind of man
are you, Joe?

20:55.950 --> 20:58.300
A man of his word
or one who's out for himself?

20:58.344 --> 21:00.563
Well, let's talk numbers.
I'll give you a good deal.

21:00.607 --> 21:02.217
I'll give you 10 grand.

21:03.784 --> 21:06.177
- For a down payment?
- For your bone marrow.

21:07.353 --> 21:09.355
Who the hell are you?

21:09.398 --> 21:10.878
It's a generous offer,

21:10.921 --> 21:13.533
considering you signed up
to do it for free.

21:13.576 --> 21:15.535
All right, look.

21:15.578 --> 21:18.015
I told that lady a price
to get her off my back.

21:18.059 --> 21:19.539
I'm not gonna do it
for 10 grand,

21:19.582 --> 21:21.323
and I'm not gonna do it
for 100 grand,

21:21.367 --> 21:22.411
so tell her to lay off.

21:23.760 --> 21:27.155
Wrong answer.

21:27.198 --> 21:28.461
You wanna try again?

21:28.504 --> 21:30.767
No.

21:30.811 --> 21:32.682
I'm done talking with you

21:32.726 --> 21:35.468
and any other pit bull
she decides to sic on me.

21:37.252 --> 21:39.733
So stop wasting my time.

21:39.776 --> 21:42.953
And tell that woman
to stay the hell away from me!

21:42.997 --> 21:49.743
<i>♪</i>

21:57.794 --> 22:04.453
<i>♪</i>

22:22.776 --> 22:24.604
There she is.

22:24.647 --> 22:26.432
Hey.

22:26.475 --> 22:28.434
Oh, I was wondering
when you were gonna call me.

22:28.477 --> 22:29.783
How you been?

22:29.826 --> 22:31.654
Oh, you know,
moving and grooving.

22:31.698 --> 22:33.656
Yeah, and have you
been moving

22:33.700 --> 22:35.005
any of that Molly
I gave you?

22:36.659 --> 22:38.618
That's what I wanted
to talk to you about.

22:39.488 --> 22:41.751
It's still
a little risky for me,

22:41.795 --> 22:44.058
but I mean,
I'd still love to be

22:44.101 --> 22:46.103
a cocktail waitress for you.

22:47.104 --> 22:51.021
Yeah, well, see,
that's a little risky for me,

22:51.065 --> 22:54.329
what with your situation
at all.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.592
But you can make decent money
selling this stuff.

22:56.636 --> 22:58.289
Tonight you can make
two grand easy.

22:58.333 --> 22:59.421
You'll be a natural.

23:00.553 --> 23:02.555
- Really?
- Yeah.

23:04.470 --> 23:07.298
Hey, has anyone seen Molly?

23:07.342 --> 23:10.563
<i>♪</i>

23:10.606 --> 23:13.130
That's your cue.

23:13.174 --> 23:15.742
Wait up.
Molly's coming your way, baby.

23:17.613 --> 23:21.530
It's gonna be the easiest thing
you've ever done.

23:21.574 --> 23:25.621
<i>♪</i>

23:25.665 --> 23:27.449
Ready?

23:27.493 --> 23:29.669
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah?

23:29.712 --> 23:31.453
Yeah. Yeah.

23:31.497 --> 23:32.628
Okay.

23:32.672 --> 23:34.935
Have fun.

23:34.978 --> 23:37.459
Come on, girl!

23:37.503 --> 23:40.070
It's Molly time!

23:40.114 --> 23:41.289
Come on, gimme, gimme, gimme.

23:41.332 --> 23:42.638
<i>♪</i>

23:42.682 --> 23:45.728
Now we can party.

23:45.772 --> 23:47.948
<i>♪</i>

23:49.210 --> 23:51.255
There I did it.

23:51.299 --> 23:52.996
It was easy, right?

23:54.694 --> 23:56.522
Hey, wait, hold on.

23:56.565 --> 23:58.567
Sit down.

23:58.611 --> 24:00.961
Let me get you a coffee
or something, huh?

24:01.004 --> 24:02.789
I don't want anything
from you

24:21.721 --> 24:24.158
<i>Hey! Hey!</i>

24:26.203 --> 24:27.378
Stop!

24:27.422 --> 24:29.685
<i>♪</i>

24:37.388 --> 24:43.830
<i>♪</i>

24:46.615 --> 24:48.095
There's your retainer.

24:48.138 --> 24:50.967
Let's get
Chris' paperwork started.

24:51.011 --> 24:53.187
<i>♪</i>

24:54.623 --> 24:56.233
And there you have it,

24:56.277 --> 24:58.148
Councilman Knight
taking a hefty kickback

24:58.192 --> 25:00.150
from a Vegas
real estate developer.

25:00.194 --> 25:02.805
And we've got a recording
from Garrett's cleaning lady

25:02.849 --> 25:04.111
to back up
what we're looking at.

25:04.154 --> 25:06.243
Booyah. Proof of a bribe.

25:06.287 --> 25:08.028
And you did this by the book?

25:08.071 --> 25:09.725
You didn't go off
the reservation?

25:09.769 --> 25:12.249
Stayed in my tepee
the whole time, Kemosabe.

25:13.207 --> 25:16.210
Well, then I'd say we have
enough to get a search warrant

25:16.253 --> 25:17.820
for Knight's home and office

25:17.864 --> 25:19.561
and anywhere else
he lays his head.

25:19.605 --> 25:21.041
Mm-hmm.

25:21.084 --> 25:22.477
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

25:22.521 --> 25:25.175
Come on, come on.

25:25.219 --> 25:28.439
Somebody's feeling themselves.
Come on, now.

25:28.483 --> 25:30.790
How'd it go?
Well, you were right.

25:30.833 --> 25:33.575
He's a stubborn son of a bitch
who won't listen to reason.

25:33.619 --> 25:34.620
What did he say?

25:34.663 --> 25:36.230
Well, you can
ask him yourself.

25:40.234 --> 25:41.452
Oh, no.

25:41.496 --> 25:43.193
I asked you

25:43.237 --> 25:45.761
to talk to him,
not kidnap him.

25:45.805 --> 25:46.893
I talked to him,
but he's an ass, all right?

25:46.936 --> 25:48.459
This way, he can think
about his actions.

25:48.503 --> 25:50.026
You shouldn't have done this.

25:50.070 --> 25:51.680
And he shouldn't have
left you in the lurch.

25:51.724 --> 25:52.681
All right,
now he's got a chance

25:52.725 --> 25:53.769
to make things right.

25:53.813 --> 25:56.772
<i>♪</i>

25:56.816 --> 25:58.208
Go on.

25:58.252 --> 26:03.779
<i>♪</i>

26:03.823 --> 26:05.825
Joe, I--

26:05.868 --> 26:07.740
<i>♪</i>

26:07.783 --> 26:10.090
I am so sorry.

26:10.133 --> 26:11.787
You should be ashamed
of yourself.

26:11.831 --> 26:14.050
<i>♪</i>

26:14.094 --> 26:15.225
I didn't ask him to do this.

26:15.269 --> 26:16.618
You know, it's peoplelike you

26:16.662 --> 26:18.272
who give immigrants
a bad name.

26:18.315 --> 26:20.796
You come here.
You take what you want.

26:20.840 --> 26:23.233
Hey, you need my bone marrow?
Just suck it right out of me.

26:23.277 --> 26:24.887
No.

26:24.931 --> 26:28.282
I came here
because you were the only match

26:28.325 --> 26:32.678
out of 35 million people
on the bone marrow registry.

26:32.721 --> 26:36.116
And it felt to me
like a miracle.

26:36.159 --> 26:37.813
But after six days
of chemotherapy

26:37.857 --> 26:41.643
to prep for the transplant,
you just disappeared.

26:41.687 --> 26:45.473
You quit and left my son
with nothing.

26:45.516 --> 26:47.910
<i>♪</i>

26:47.954 --> 26:49.825
Can you imagine
what it feels like

26:49.869 --> 26:52.132
to have a child who could die?

26:52.175 --> 26:55.701
Joe, you have a daughter.

26:56.702 --> 27:00.531
Wouldn't you do everything
you could to save her?

27:00.575 --> 27:01.924
Don't go there.

27:01.968 --> 27:03.839
I'm not gonna let you
manipulate me like she did.

27:03.883 --> 27:05.841
How could you just
turn your back on us

27:05.885 --> 27:07.495
when you could save his life?

27:07.538 --> 27:11.673
<i>♪</i>

27:11.717 --> 27:13.719
I am not going to risk my life

27:13.762 --> 27:15.590
for a couple of strangers.

27:15.634 --> 27:18.680
<i>♪</i>

27:18.724 --> 27:21.944
Donating is safe and easy, Joe.

27:21.988 --> 27:23.642
It won't be painful at all.

27:25.295 --> 27:27.689
You won't even have
to take time off work.

27:27.733 --> 27:29.691
What do you think
is happening now?

27:29.735 --> 27:35.697
<i>♪</i>

27:35.741 --> 27:37.568
You're right.

27:37.612 --> 27:38.787
I'm sorry.

27:41.007 --> 27:44.706
I never intended for things
to get out of hand like this.

27:44.750 --> 27:46.316
Really?

27:46.360 --> 27:48.928
Then let me go.

27:48.971 --> 27:54.716
<i>♪</i>

27:57.371 --> 27:58.633
We have to let him go.

27:58.677 --> 27:59.895
Absolutely not.

27:59.939 --> 28:00.722
Let him think about it
for a while,

28:00.766 --> 28:02.724
he's gonna change his mind.

28:02.768 --> 28:04.770
- We can't force him.
- You have no choice.

28:04.813 --> 28:06.293
You have to do this for Luca.

28:06.336 --> 28:08.208
I'm not gonna
steal his bone marrow.

28:10.166 --> 28:11.385
One second.

28:11.428 --> 28:12.734
What's up, Eric?
I'm busy.

28:12.778 --> 28:14.954
I'm being raided by feds,
lots of them.

28:14.997 --> 28:16.564
Listen, you have to get
my laptop out of Lexi's room.

28:16.607 --> 28:17.870
<i>
What are you talking about?</i>

28:17.913 --> 28:19.132
They're not gonna
find anything here,

28:19.175 --> 28:20.437
but trust me, you do not
want the FBI to know

28:20.481 --> 28:21.743
what's in my laptop, okay?

28:21.787 --> 28:23.136
Just calm down.

28:23.179 --> 28:24.790
<i>You're gonna keep</i> <i>
your mouth shut</i>

28:24.833 --> 28:26.356
<i>until your lawyers</i> <i>
are with you, you understand?</i>

28:26.400 --> 28:28.010
Go, go, go!

28:28.054 --> 28:29.446
<i>And we're gonna</i> <i>
get you out of this, man.</i>

28:29.490 --> 28:34.016
<i>♪</i>

28:34.060 --> 28:36.932
All right, hey, come on.
I need your help.

28:36.976 --> 28:39.761
Well, what about him?
We can't leave him here.

28:39.805 --> 28:41.981
It'll do him some good
to stew on things for a while.

28:42.024 --> 28:44.200
Come on, let's go.
We're going back to the hotel.

28:44.244 --> 28:45.767
I you need to get something
from Lexi's room.

28:45.811 --> 28:48.944
<i>♪</i>

28:55.734 --> 28:57.605
Why can't his girlfriendget it?

28:57.648 --> 28:58.954
She's out of town.

28:58.998 --> 29:00.216
If the feds get their hands
on that laptop,

29:00.260 --> 29:01.914
it'll implicate us.

29:01.957 --> 29:04.046
What if someone
catches me?

29:04.090 --> 29:06.266
Just say you're cleaning
the room, then get out.

29:06.309 --> 29:08.442
And remember, you're gonna have
to go down to the lobby,

29:08.485 --> 29:10.792
then back up
to the hotel suites, all right?

29:10.836 --> 29:13.490
2006, Be quick.

29:13.534 --> 29:19.801
<i>♪</i>

29:31.030 --> 29:32.858
Lexi Torres,
it's the FBI. Open up.

29:32.901 --> 29:37.514
<i>♪</i>

29:38.733 --> 29:39.995
Did you hear something?

29:40.039 --> 29:46.785
<i>♪</i>

29:51.093 --> 29:53.052
FBI.

29:53.095 --> 29:56.098
Lexi Torres, if you are here,
show yourself now.

29:56.142 --> 30:02.888
<i>♪</i>

30:48.759 --> 30:50.065
Renée.

30:50.109 --> 30:57.029
<i>♪</i>

31:08.127 --> 31:09.911
Let's go.

31:09.955 --> 31:15.743
<i>♪</i>

31:20.226 --> 31:21.967
Hey.

31:25.796 --> 31:26.972
Sorry.

31:27.015 --> 31:31.367
<i>♪</i>

31:31.411 --> 31:34.849
Right.
Of course, yeah.

31:34.893 --> 31:35.894
Come on, let's go.

31:37.025 --> 31:37.983
You got it?

31:39.549 --> 31:40.942
No one saw you?

31:45.381 --> 31:47.253
This will pull you
a lot of favors from Hayak.

31:49.168 --> 31:51.126
You really got us
out of a bind here.

31:51.170 --> 31:53.041
I'll let him know
what you did for us.

31:56.088 --> 31:57.393
What do you wanna do with him?

32:07.490 --> 32:09.101
Get up.

32:09.144 --> 32:10.841
Hey, come on, get up.

32:16.021 --> 32:17.892
So what are you
gonna do now?

32:17.936 --> 32:19.589
Drain me of my bone marrow
and then dump me in the desert?

32:19.633 --> 32:20.764
That the plan?

32:20.808 --> 32:22.244
I'm taking you home.

32:22.288 --> 32:27.423
<i>♪</i>

32:27.467 --> 32:30.209
All right, listen, jackass.

32:30.252 --> 32:31.253
I know where you work.

32:32.820 --> 32:33.995
I know where you live.

32:35.214 --> 32:36.258
You understand me?

32:36.302 --> 32:39.653
<i>♪</i>

32:39.696 --> 32:40.871
Ah.

32:40.915 --> 32:47.661
<i>♪</i>

33:08.508 --> 33:10.553
My wife went in
for a simple procedure.

33:16.081 --> 33:18.039
They told her it would be safe
and easy too.

33:22.304 --> 33:25.655
Small hernia operation,
no big deal.

33:25.699 --> 33:29.050
<i>♪</i>

33:29.094 --> 33:31.226
I watched her walk
into the patient room.

33:31.270 --> 33:33.924
<i>♪</i>

33:33.968 --> 33:35.665
And she never came out.

33:35.709 --> 33:40.670
<i>♪</i>

33:40.714 --> 33:42.759
I'm sorry.

33:42.803 --> 33:45.893
Yeah.

33:45.936 --> 33:47.329
The lawyers
representing the hospital

33:47.373 --> 33:49.070
said they were sorry too.

33:50.332 --> 33:52.160
So did the doctors.

33:53.944 --> 33:56.599
Everyone was sorry.

34:01.300 --> 34:03.911
After that my, daughter and I
stopped talking to each other.

34:03.954 --> 34:06.000
<i>♪</i>

34:06.044 --> 34:07.480
She kept saying,

34:07.523 --> 34:10.309
"Suing the hospital
isn't going to bring her back."

34:10.352 --> 34:14.878
<i>♪</i>

34:14.922 --> 34:16.967
Ah, it was all my fault,
really.

34:17.011 --> 34:20.319
<i>♪</i>

34:20.362 --> 34:23.713
I was just so angry.

34:23.757 --> 34:26.325
<i>♪</i>

34:26.368 --> 34:27.935
Angry at the world.

34:27.978 --> 34:31.547
<i>♪</i>

34:31.591 --> 34:34.594
How can you not be so angry

34:34.637 --> 34:36.509
at what's happening
to your son?

34:36.552 --> 34:39.338
<i>♪</i>

34:39.381 --> 34:41.514
How can you just...

34:41.557 --> 34:44.778
live your life
without hating everyone?

34:44.821 --> 34:47.259
<i>♪</i>

34:47.302 --> 34:50.740
As long as I have my son,
I have to have hope.

34:50.784 --> 34:53.917
<i>♪</i>

34:55.571 --> 34:59.401
<i>♪</i>

34:59.445 --> 35:01.969
My wife was the glue
in our family.

35:02.012 --> 35:03.797
<i>♪</i>

35:03.840 --> 35:05.190
Without her--

35:07.975 --> 35:10.282
Oh, damn it, what happened?

35:11.239 --> 35:13.154
Flat tire.

35:13.198 --> 35:15.330
Here, pull over to the side.

35:21.467 --> 35:23.556
Don't suppose you know
how to change a tire?

35:26.907 --> 35:29.518
I made sure that Grace knew

35:29.562 --> 35:31.477
how to do general maintenance
on a car.

35:36.221 --> 35:38.397
I think more fathers

35:38.440 --> 35:40.138
should teach their daughters
this stuff.

35:42.227 --> 35:43.489
Your dad never taught you?

35:45.621 --> 35:49.408
Well, my dad was a doctorwho died

35:49.451 --> 35:52.324
at the hands of the Khmer Rouge
before I was born.

35:55.283 --> 35:59.548
But my mother never stopped
telling me how brave he was

35:59.592 --> 36:03.161
and how he would risk
his life for others.

36:04.640 --> 36:06.294
That's why I became a doctor.

36:09.254 --> 36:11.821
Guess that tops knowing
how to change a tire.

36:17.479 --> 36:19.046
It's my son.

36:20.656 --> 36:22.267
Hey, peanut, you okay?

36:22.310 --> 36:25.444
<i>Can you sing me</i> <i>
to sleep, Mommy?</i>

36:25.487 --> 36:27.663
Of course.
How could I forget?

36:27.707 --> 36:30.275
Put the phone on the pillow.

36:30.318 --> 36:32.277
Yeah, and close your eyes.

36:47.379 --> 36:53.646
<i>♪</i>

37:05.223 --> 37:07.703
Okay. I love you.

37:10.750 --> 37:17.496
<i>♪</i>

37:29.986 --> 37:34.469
That lullaby
you were singing.

37:34.513 --> 37:40.170
<i>♪</i>

37:42.347 --> 37:45.654
It was the same song that
my wife would sing to Grace

37:45.698 --> 37:47.917
whenever she got fussy.

37:47.961 --> 37:54.881
<i>♪</i>

37:54.924 --> 37:57.536
She always loved her mama
more than me.

37:57.579 --> 38:00.190
<i>♪</i>

38:00.234 --> 38:02.715
Even when she was a baby.

38:02.758 --> 38:09.504
<i>♪</i>

38:13.378 --> 38:14.422
Turn around.

38:16.032 --> 38:17.251
Why?

38:17.295 --> 38:19.253
<i>♪</i>

38:19.297 --> 38:20.646
We're going back to Vegas.

38:21.864 --> 38:23.779
I changed my mind.

38:23.823 --> 38:25.607
<i>♪</i>

38:25.651 --> 38:27.392
I want to help you
and your boy.

38:27.435 --> 38:29.829
<i>♪</i>

38:29.872 --> 38:31.396
Okay?

38:31.439 --> 38:35.400
<i>♪</i>

38:35.443 --> 38:38.620
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

38:38.664 --> 38:45.410
<i>♪</i>

39:02.470 --> 39:09.129
<i>♪</i>

39:27.669 --> 39:34.284
<i>♪</i>

39:37.287 --> 39:44.033
<i>♪</i>

39:47.559 --> 39:49.909
<i>Get some rest now, baby.</i>

39:54.261 --> 39:56.698
That was amazing, Fiona.
Yeah?

39:56.742 --> 39:58.657
Yeah, just like
my Lola's cooking.

39:58.700 --> 40:00.267
This whole house
reminds me of her.

40:00.310 --> 40:01.268
Smells the same.

40:01.311 --> 40:02.922
Told you, Mom,

40:02.965 --> 40:04.619
the house smells like
an old lady's house.

40:04.663 --> 40:06.665
- Chris!
- Shh, boy

40:06.708 --> 40:08.231
Rude much?

40:08.275 --> 40:10.277
Well, my Lola was a great
cook, just like your mom.

40:10.320 --> 40:12.540
Mm-hmm. Mm!

40:15.325 --> 40:17.937
Mind if I have another?
Oh, okay.

40:17.980 --> 40:20.243
I like my beer.
Yeah.

40:20.287 --> 40:21.593
So don't think you're getting
my liver next,

40:21.636 --> 40:23.551
'cause it's already pickled.

40:23.595 --> 40:25.031
I still don't know how Thony

40:25.074 --> 40:26.902
talked you into donating
your bone marrow,

40:26.946 --> 40:28.904
but thank God she did.

40:34.780 --> 40:38.523
Well, who would I be if I
didn't help out my <i>kabayan?</i>

40:38.566 --> 40:41.700
Mm-hmm.

40:41.743 --> 40:43.615
My Filipina sisters.

40:48.750 --> 40:51.579
So, Joe, I have
a surprise for you.

40:51.623 --> 40:53.886
No, thanks, I don't want
any more surprises from you.

40:53.929 --> 40:55.278
This is a good one.

40:55.322 --> 40:57.150
I thought you might like
someone else

40:57.193 --> 40:58.543
driving you back home.

41:05.027 --> 41:06.594
Grace?

41:06.638 --> 41:12.731
<i>♪</i>

41:12.774 --> 41:15.168
I told her
what you did for Luca.

41:15.211 --> 41:17.692
I'm so proud of you, Tatay.

41:17.736 --> 41:24.525
<i>♪</i>

41:33.752 --> 41:34.535
Thank you.

41:34.579 --> 41:41.586
<i>♪</i>

41:48.810 --> 41:51.596
I hate this place.
It's filthy.

41:51.639 --> 41:53.772
What, you think
I like this place?

41:53.815 --> 41:54.860
Listen, just don't worry, okay?

41:54.903 --> 41:56.426
I'm gonna be out here
in no time.

41:56.470 --> 41:57.253
And when I get out of here,
I'm gonna take care of you,

41:57.297 --> 41:58.559
so just sit tight.

42:02.258 --> 42:03.564
Oh, my God.

42:19.232 --> 42:25.891
<i>♪</i>

42:35.509 --> 42:36.815
Agent Miller.

42:41.863 --> 42:44.649
<i>♪</i>

42:44.692 --> 42:46.781
Ah, son of a bitch!

42:50.045 --> 42:56.704
<i>♪</i>

43:26.081 --> 43:32.740
<i>♪</i>
